Package: RateScape
Title: Detecting Rate Heterogeneity in Discrete Character Evolution
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
  person("Heath", "Blackmon", role = c("aut", "cre"),
         email = "h-blackmon@tamu.edu",
         comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5433-4036")),
  person("Claude", "Opus", role = "ctb", comment = "AI-assisted implementation")
  )
Description: RateScape provides Bayesian and maximum likelihood methods for
  detecting and estimating rate heterogeneity in discrete character evolution
  across phylogenetic trees. The package allows users to specify complex
  rate matrices (Q matrices) and infer branch-specific rate scalars, enabling
  the visualization of rate-shifted lineages on painted phylogenies. Implements
  spike-and-slab mixture models (Bayesian) and discretized gamma categories (ML)
  with comprehensive prior specification tools and diagnostic functions.
